## ðŸ” Diagnostic Criteria

### Must Have (Essential)
1.  Urinary frequency with copious, pale urine and/or incontinence.
2.  General or localized signs of Cold (cold limbs, aversion to cold, cold lower back).
3.  Pale, wet tongue and a deep, weak, slow pulse.

### Usually Has (Common)
- Nocturia or enuresis
- Lower back soreness and weakness
- Lassitude and fatigue

### May Have (Variable)
- Dizziness
- Tinnitus
- Pale complexion

